      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear-elastic titanium alloy model with nonlinear contact at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces; geometric nonlinearity enabled for large-displacement regime.",
      "rationale": "Titanium Ti-6Al-4V modeled as linear elastic (E=114 GPa, nu=0.34) consistent with published material data and low strain levels observed experimentally. Nonlinear contact (penalty method, friction mu=0.15) at all interfaces. Geometric nonlinearity enabled. Model form appropriate for the QoIs and loading regime. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
