      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 non-cannulated constructs from production lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing; two independent laboratories.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH OSEL and DePuy Synthes test facility). All constructs from production lots; 100% dimensional inspection performed. Inter-laboratory variability characterized. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate in vivo loading environment across a range of load magnitudes and rates representative of clinical use.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standardized test condition (quasi-static, 5 mm/min crosshead displacement). While the standardized condition is well-characterized, only one test configuration was evaluated, limiting coverage of the clinical loading space. Gradation 2 achieved; below required Gradation 3. This shortfall is acknowledged and mitigated by the conservative nature of ASTM F1717 loading relative to in vivo conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
