      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; acceptance bound E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs; percent difference < 10% for mean values.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison performed using the validation metric E/uval per ASME V&V 40 Section 7. For all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm): E/uval values are 0.81, 1.44, and 1.72 respectively, all within the 1.96 acceptance bound. Percent differences are 4.2%, 7.8%, and 9.1%, all within the 10% bound. Gradation 3 achieved."
